Ones Twos ThreesShow how it works Fours Fives Sixes Three of a kind Four of a kind Little Straight Big Straight House Chance Payment
You have 12 rounds to play that game. At, first you have to role the dices. This can be done by moving the phone. You can repeat "shaking" at least 3 times. If you think you have a good setup,
you can choose the best possible combination from a list by clicking the dices. A long press on a dice selects every dice that has the same number and writes down the points. A normal click selects the dices you touch and try to find a "Three of a kind", "Four of a kind", "Little Straight", "Big Straight", or "House" and calculates the points. This has to be done in every round. However, it isn’t possible to select the same combination twice. If there is no combination than you get 0 points.
You get rewarded based on the sum of their reported scores, providing an incentive to lie: • $0:50 : below 150 points • $1:00 : between 150 and 200 points • $2:00 : more than 200 points
